Data for Elektro Ljubljana outages
==================================

This repository contains data on electrical substation outages and
number of clients without electrical power in the first half of February 2014.
It covers the regions in central and southern Slovenia (including the capital
Ljubljana) and is based on public reports released by Elektro Ljubljana, the
electrical distribution company supplying these regions.

In Slovenia in end of January 2014 heavy snow and glaze ice caused wide spread
damage to electrical distribution network. A power outage because of fallen
trees and collapsed overhead power lines affected approximately one fifth of
the population. In some regions it took more than two weeks before emergency
repairs could be put in place.

Contents:

extract.json - Extracted and cleaned-up data in JSON format.

scrape       - Original reports (some of the files have had HTML markup
               minimally corrected for easier data extraction)

Makefile     - Contains rules for extracting the JSON file from HTML files and
	       visualizing the data in a graph and an animation.

